node.text:
🌀🌀Curl Chronicles⁣ 🌀🌀
⁣
My hair was desperate for a serious refresh and the Camille Rose Honey 🍯 Collection is the sweetest gift to my hair 🎁 
⁣
My curls are loving the new honey collection from @camillerosenaturals ⁣🍯 🐝 
⁣
I used the fresh honey nectar deep treatment to bring back definition and bounce and followed up with the honey leave in, honeycomb curl whip and a little bit of the spiked honey mousse for added moisture. ⁣
⁣
Best of all, I love supporting amazing sister friend entrepreneurs and black owned businesses founded by the one the only 👏🏾👏🏾@janell_stephens!⁣
⁣
You can find these products and more of the #camillerosenaturals product line at @Target stores and online at camillerose.com” ⁣

Check out my stories for a direct link to buy! 
⁣
#Camille⁣rose #honeynectar #skinaunaturale #curlcommunity

node.text:
Its TENACITY TUESDAY 🚀🚀and I am sharing a little peek at the Making of a Mogul episode with Entrepreneur @johnhopebryant!⁣
⁣
@johnhopebryant is an American Entrepreneur and humanitarian who has built more than 40 organizations, entities, and companies, including Operation HOPE amongst many others.⁣
⁣
John Hope Bryant is in the business of both re-inventing everyone to their God-given potential to be great and boundless. With a belief that every entrepreneur can 'do well and do good, too.' Better still, they can 'do well by doing good. @johnhopebryant has vowed to create one million Black entrepreneurs with the $130 million funds with Spotify. He is truly the epitome of what the making of a mogul is all about.⁣
⁣
Follow @johnhopebryant for more entrepreneurship tips, and @operationhopehq to find out about the Spotify opportunity.⁣
⁣
#makingofamogulusa⁣
⁣
Created & Directed by @ifactorylive⁣

Associate Produced by @itstanyatime 
⁣
Executive Produced by @cem_mediagroup ⁣
⁣
Produced by @samaddavis⁣
⁣
DOP @rodbreed⁣
Styling @Fiskanistyle⁣
Make up @blushgurl⁣
⁣
And the rest of the #makingofamogulusa crew⁣
⁣
#makingofamogulusa⁣
#CEMMedia ⁣
#makingofamogul ⁣
#TanyaSam⁣
#ifactorylive⁣
#enterpreneur ⁣
#atlanta

node.text:
𝐓𝐀𝐍𝐘𝐀 𝐓𝐈𝐌𝐄 𝐁𝐎𝐎𝐊 𝐂𝐋𝐔𝐁 𝐙𝐎𝐎𝐌 ⁣𝐏𝐀𝐑𝐓𝐘⁣
𝐓𝐡𝐮𝐫𝐬𝐝𝐚𝐲 𝐉𝐮𝐥𝐲 𝟐𝟐𝐧𝐝 𝐚𝐭 𝟖𝐩𝐦 𝐄𝐓⁣🍷🎉⁣
⁣
𝐑𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐤 𝐢𝐧 𝐁𝐈𝐎 and in my stories!! ⁣ 📚 You must register for the Zoom, it will not on IG Live⁣
⁣⁣
Hey BookClubbers!! ⁣⁣
⁣
What a great month discussing Seven Days in June by Tia Williams and I can’t wait to cyber -see everyone this Thursday for our virtual ZOOM Party!! This book was amazing and I loved talking all about Eva, Shane and their delicious love story and of course, Audre!!⁣
⁣
This is your chance to ask and interact with the author herself!  Get the inside scoop on everything that went into writing one of our favorite books to date! ⁣
⁣
Anyone can join - even if you did not tune into the weekly IG Lives! ⁣
⁣
XOXO⁣
Tanya⁣
⁣
Ps.  Don’t forget to stay for the “after-party” where we get to virtual shoot the breeze and talk anything and everything fun, from books, TV, and more!  I am currently watching African movie on Netflix in Accra!⁣
⁣⁣
#TanyaTimeBookClub #virtualBookClub #SevenDaysInJune #tiaWilliams #tanyatimebookclub

‘Ɛ𝘆ɛ’ - “𝗜 𝗮𝗺 𝗙𝗜𝗡𝗘” ⁣
⁣
🇬🇭The response to Ɛte sɛn? / Wo ho te sɛn? “How are you?” in Twi is ‘Ɛyɛ‘ meaning ‘I’m fine’⁣
⁣
😉 ⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣

node.text:
Ɛte sɛn? / Wo ho te sɛn? 

- a Twi term that means ‘how are you? ✨⁣

My dad is from the Ga tribe and speaks Ga.  Unfortunately, I do not speak the language but as I grew up hearing all my life I can understand a good deal. 

The most widely used languages spoken here are Ga and Twi. 
⁣
#GhanaGirl 💃🏽 #accra #accraghana #wanderlust #travel #beyondthereturn  #yearofthereturn 🇬🇭✨#africatotheworld #instatravel

node.text:
FOR THE CULTURE 🇬🇭✊🏾❤️⁣
⁣
Today I had the privilege of meeting with the and having some truly fascinating and exciting conversations about Ghana and the future of the African Diaspora with @mokrakumantey, the Hon. Deputy Minister for Tourism Arts and Culture and Mr. Akwasi Awua Ababio, the Director of the Diaspora for the Office of the President! ⁣
⁣
From the bottom of my heart we invite you back to Ghana 🇬🇭. Excited to share more things to come ❤️💛💚⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
#beyondTheReturn #bigThingsareComing⁣
#YEAROFTHERETURN #Decaadeofthereturn #Ghana #accraGhana #comeHOME #ghanagirls #travel #wanderlust #explore 

Thank you @theimagebureau @georgequaye  for setting up such great connections 
📸 @manuelphotography_official

node.text:
🇬🇭✨

This picture pretty much sums up how I feel right now, every cell of my body just bursting with love and joy and the culture of my Ghanaian roots. ⁣
 
Africa is so full of life; love, dance, music, food, family and beauty and I feel so grateful to be right here, right now, able to soak it all in. ⁣
⁣
BE HERE NOW!⁣ but Follow my IG stories for more fun and Ghana day to day life 
⁣
#ghanagirlGLOW #ghana
